China is close to completing its first blood bank for pandas, aiding in research on their blood types and transfusion acceptance.
The bank, located in a breeding lab, will enhance genetic diversity.
The Qinling panda, a sub-species of the giant panda, resides in the Qinling mountains.
With only around 1,600 pandas in the wild, efforts are being made to protect and preserve these endangered animals.
Giant pandas in various reserves face challenges such as blooming bamboo affecting their food supply.
Conservation efforts, including nature reserves and habitat protection, are crucial for the survival of these iconic creatures.
